OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781923667
OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to quit after
OL,4,CBurnham's by-election win
OL,6,FSome in Westminster believe a contest
OL,7,Fcould begin as early as next week but
OL,8,Fallies of Mr Burnham favour a longer
OL,9,Fwait to allow them to prepare for
OL,10,Fgovernment.
OL,12,FFormer transport secretary Louise
OL,13,FHaigh, one of his supporters, said
OL,14,Fafter his by-election victory: "We
OL,15,Freally hope that this can be a managed
OL,16,Fand orderly transition and Keir
OL,17,FStarmer will reflect on the results,
OL,18,Fand Andy and Keir can meet in the
OL,19,Fcoming days, and over the next week,
OL,20,Fand agree a path forward."
OL,26,@vD@`OU|D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
